若疫情全球蔓延，或致全球经济损失1.1万亿美元。
If the epidemic spreads globally, it could cause global economic losses of $1.1 trillion.
财经十一人                      。
Eleven finance and economics.
财经十一人。
Eleven finance and economics.
由《财经》杂志公司产业报道团队创建，研讨企业成败，探究行业兴衰，推动阳光商业。
Founded by Caijing magazine's industry report team, it explores the success or failure of enterprises, probes into the ups and downs of the industry, and promotes sunshine business.
The following article comes from 巴伦。
The following article comes from Barents.
Author 瑞什马·帕迪。
Author Rishma Paddy.
巴伦。
Baron.
中国最具影响力的财经新闻媒体《财经》携手道琼斯媒体集团，引入百年历史的《巴伦》（Barron's）独家内容，打造涵盖全球金融信息、市场动态、行业分析、公司研究及理财顾问评估的全球投资平台。
China's most influential financial news media, Caijing, teamed up with Dow Jones Media Group to introduce the 100-year-old Barron & amp; apos; s exclusive content to create a global investment platform that covers global financial information, market dynamics, industry analysis, corporate research and financial advisory assessments.
。
.
牛津经济研究所估计，如果最坏情景出现，病毒演变为一场全球疫情，那么2020年全球经济将损失1.1万亿美元。
If, in the worst-case scenario, the virus evolves into a global epidemic, the Oxford Economic Research Institute estimates that the global economy could lose $1.1 trillion by 2020.
面对如此多的不确定性，情景规划是投资者应对潜在形势的最佳方式——尤其是在目前市场基本乐观的情况下文 | 瑞什马·帕迪编辑 | 张晓添大多数经济学家和策略师认为，新型冠状病毒将在未来几周得到遏制，并且中国当局将推出一项计划以缓解经济冲击。
In the face of so much uncertainty, scenario planning is the best way for investors to cope with the underlying situation - especially at a time when markets are generally optimistic. & # 160; Most economists and strategists believe that the new coronavirus will be contained in the coming weeks, and that Chinese authorities will launch a plan to mitigate the economic shock.
但是，牛津经济研究所(Oxford Economics)估计，如果最坏情景出现，病毒演变为一场全球疫情，那么2020年全球经济将损失1.1万亿美元。
But the Oxford Economics estimates that if the worst happens and the virus evolves into a global epidemic, the global economy could lose $1.1 trillion by 2020.
本周新确诊感染病例数量一直在下降，但医学专家警告说，现在就断言疫情的危险已经解除还为时过早。
The number of new infections confirmed this week has been declining, but medical experts warn it is too early to say that the risk of an outbreak has been removed.
截至发稿，已有近75300例确诊病例，超过2000人死亡。
By the time of writing, there had been nearly 75,300 confirmed cases, with more than 2,000 deaths.
面对如此多的不确定性，情景规划是投资者应对潜在形势的最佳方式——尤其是在目前市场基本乐观的情况下。
In the face of so much uncertainty, scenario planning is the best way for investors to cope with the potential situation - especially given the prevailing optimism in the markets.
标普500指数今年迄今已上涨近5%，而追踪中国公司的iShares MSCI China ETF(MCHI)今年迄今已上涨1.6%。
The S & P 500 is up nearly 5 per cent so far this year, while iShares MSCI China ETF (MCHI), which tracks Chinese companies, is up 1.6 per cent so far this year.
人们预计，中国政府将出台更多刺激措施以帮助遭受重创的企业，这给投资者带来了一些安慰。
Investors have some comfort in the expectation that the government will introduce more stimulus measures to help battered businesses.
牛津经济研究所首席经济学家亚当·斯莱特(Adam Slater)在给客户的一份报告中写道，如果疫情蔓延至全球，上半年的经济增长或将降至近乎于零，美国和欧元区或将进入“技术性衰退”。
'If the epidemic spreads around the world, economic growth in the first half of this year could fall to near zero, and the United States and the euro zone could enter a 'technical recession,' Adam Slater, chief economist at the Oxford Institute of Economics, wrote in a report to clients.
这可能使2020年全球经济增速较2.3%的基线预期减少1.3个百分点，但可能会迅速复苏；而全球GDP仍将按照2021年增长2.9%的基线预期增长。
This could reduce global economic growth by 1.3 percentage points from the baseline forecast of 2.3 per cent in 2020, but could lead to a rapid recovery, while global GDP is still expected to grow at a baseline rate of 2.9 per cent in 2021.
根据该机构的预测，如果疫情仅限于亚洲，那么2020年全球GDP或将从基线预测下降4000亿美元，或0.5个百分点。
According to the agency's projections, if the epidemic is limited to Asia, global GDP could fall by $400 billion, or 0.5 percentage points, from the baseline forecast in 2020.
亚太地区的经济增长率或将从2019年底的4%下降到2020年上半年的1.5%，那将是自全球金融危机以来的最低水平。
Economic growth in the Asia-Pacific region is likely to fall from 4 per cent at the end of 2019 to 1.5 per cent in the first half of 2020, the lowest rate since the global financial crisis.
这些情景是基于过去SARS和“猪流感”等疫情的经验，并假设经济方面痛苦将来自多个方面：人们生病时可支配开支降低；旅行限制继续施行，人们避免外出；许多人无法工作导致生产受阻；出行和旅游支出急剧下降。
These scenarios are based on past experiences with epidemics such as SARS and swine flu, and assume that economic pain will come from many sources: lower disposable costs when people get sick; continued travel restrictions that prevent people from going out; production disruptions due to the inability of many people to work; and sharp declines in travel and tourism expenditures.
它还假定，由于不确定性、需求下降、供应链中断以及金融风险蔓延，投资水平将会降低，同时股价走低、货币市场利差上升。
It also assumes that, owing to uncertainty, falling demand, supply chain disruptions and the spread of financial risks, investment levels will decline, while stock prices will fall and money market spreads will rise.
不过，投资者普遍认为，经济将出现“V”型复苏——起初会遭受猛烈打击，然后在疫情得到遏制后迅速、大幅复苏。
However, investors generally believe that there will be a "V-shaped" recovery - one that will initially be hard hit and then recover quickly and dramatically once the epidemic is contained.
部分理由是，有观点认为，中国政府正在出台刺激措施以减轻经济遭受的沉重打击——从提供财政援助，到帮助工厂与科技公司建立联系，从而发现它们供应链中的薄弱环节。
Part of the reason is the perception that Beijing is rolling out stimulus measures to soften the blow to the economy - from providing financial aid to helping factories connect with technology companies to uncover weaknesses in their supply chains.
但凯投宏观(Capital Economics)的朱利安·埃文斯-普里查德(Julian Evans-Pritchard)在给客户的另一份报告中写道，就业形势可能会阻碍经济迅速反弹的能力。
But Julian Evans-Pritchard of Capital Economics wrote in a separate report to clients that the employment situation could hamper the economy's ability to rebound quickly.
据智联招聘的一项调查显示，尽管中国绝大多数上市公司有足够的资金维持至少两三个月的债务相关开支和薪酬开支，但13%的公司已经开始裁员。
While the vast majority of Chinese listed companies have enough capital to cover at least two or three months of debt-related expenses and payroll expenses, 13 per cent of companies have already started cutting jobs, according to a survey by the think tank.
同时，除非经济活动“很快”反弹，否则失业情况还会进一步加剧。
At the same time, unemployment will worsen unless economic activity rebounds "quickly."
埃文斯-普里查德(Evans-Pritchard)写道，中国自营职业或经营小型家庭企业的城市劳动力的当季收入将大幅下降，而那些离开原岗位、寻找新工作的外出务工者将找不到新工作。
'Urban workers who are self-employed or run small family businesses in China will see their earnings fall sharply in the current quarter, 'Mr. Evans-Pritchard writes, while migrant workers who leave their jobs in search of new jobs won't find new ones.
在上市公司中，最脆弱的是房地产开发商。
Among the listed companies, the most vulnerable are real estate developers.
但除了情况最差的公司，大多数应该能够经受住至少三个月的疫情。
But with the exception of the worst-performing companies, most should be able to withstand at least three months of an epidemic.
更容易受到冲击的是中小企业，这些企业约占城市就业的一半，可能不会遵守中国政府不裁员的指令。
More vulnerable are small and medium-sized enterprises, which account for about half of urban employment and may not comply with Beijing's non-layoff directive.
埃文斯-普里查德援引中国两所大学对1000家此类企业的调查称，该调查发现，除非情况有所改善，否则三分之一的企业将在一个月内耗尽资金，而两个月内耗尽资金的企业占比升至三分之二。
Unless things improve, says Evans-Pritchard, citing a survey of 1,000 such companies by two Chinese universities, a third of companies will run out of capital within a month and two-thirds will run out of capital within two months unless things improve.
结论是：很多事情目前还是未知，而经济复苏可能不会像某些人希望的那样迅速或平稳。
The conclusion is that much is still unknown, and the recovery may not be as rapid or smooth as some would like.
